++++* Escape
The Chief is awoken by the smell of death and finds themself in a sea of blood with a bestial Ninety-Nine. Usually defined by her overwhelming strength, she seems now to be struggling to endure something. The Chief tries to reach out to her, but she tells them not to follow her. Countless monsters emerge from their surroundings and Ninety-Nine destroys them all, but their corpses transform into filthy, contaminated blood that pours into her body, causing her to tear at her own skin. The Chief throws themself in front of her sword to stop her, and she pleads for them to take her away from this battle.

The Chief sees the exit to the mirage blocked by two gates. Ninety-Nine explains that there are two mechanisms that must be destroyed for it to open. She has been watching, hoping to escape, but is unable to resist the urge to fight. They make their way towards the mechanisms, Ninety-Nine obliterating many more monsters and fanatical researchers along the way, though she becomes weaker with every combat. When one mechanism is destroyed, it reforms into a massive Mania-weapon sword. When the other is destroyed, it plays a lab recording of an experiment.

Ninety-Nine urges the Chief to get out alone if she should die, but they insist that they will get her out of there alive. They finally reach the exit, and they emerge into a rain-soaked desert. The rain washes away the blood and contamination from her body. The Chief asks what she will do now, and Ninety-Nine answers that she doesn’t know, but she doesn’t want to be the person she was inside there anymore.

//She perches atop a mountain of bones and a sea of blood//
//She drops the sword in her hand.//
//And lets the rain wash away the blood.//
//Embracing her scars, she escapes from her own abyss.//
